Entering the restaurant really got my hopes up. It has the right smell for a middle eastern restaurant. The lamb shawarma meat is pretty good, not amazing, but solid. The chicken shawarma is about as bland as I have tasted. Where this restaurant truly disappoints is in how they fill the pita for the shawarma. It may be the worst approach to filling a shawarma I've ever seen, and I've been to literally hundreds of shawarma places. The way they fill it, you end up with all the salad at the bottom, the meat at the top, and the sauce (which is pretty good sauce) at really only two spots. So most bites are either all meat or all salad, and either way too much sauce or not nearly enough sauce. Thoroughly ruins the shawarma eating experience. Who wants to end the shawarma with all salad???

Once you walk in you will notice all the signs and stickers on the back wall. It's like they are encouraging to add to this and make yourself known. The decor is plain and most of your focus will be needed to search through the VAST menu.
